      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"8. ROMP TIN was below best at her last start when 6th at this track following a win (24.63) there two back. Form here at the trip sound including five wins. Can discover winning form. 5. PAW RIVAL showed blistering pace early and gave a sight when in the minors, beaten 2.25 lengths over 390m Ballarat in 22.23. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to his credit. Expected to feature again. 1. PAW RAMELLO is a talented type and proved too strong last time to win by 2 lengths at Warragul in a handy 22.94 beating Bunni Bale. Solid formlines coming through her last run. Expected to feature again. 6. CATCH A CUTIE should be thereabouts despite an unplaced run here most recently.\",\"runners\":[8,5,1,6],\"exclusive\":false}",
